<!-- Slide 6: How OpenCode loads extensions -->
<div class="content-slide deep-slide deep-slide--usage">
  <p class="overline">Runtime Extension Points</p>
  <h2>How OpenCode Loads <span class="highlight">Extensions</span></h2>
  <p class="lead deep-slide__lead">
    Skills are discovered and pulled into context on demand. Plugins are loaded into the
    runtime and called back through hooks.
  </p>

  <div class="loader-grid">
    <div class="loader-card loader-card--skill">
      <div class="loader-card__header">
        <span class="loader-card__kicker">Prompted Behavior</span>
        <h3>Skills</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="loader-card__text">
        Configured sources and conventional <code>skill/</code> or <code>skills/</code> dirs are scanned
        for <code>SKILL.md</code>. OpenCode advertises names + descriptions; the full body enters context only when selected.
      </p>
      <div class="loader-flow">
        <span class="loader-step">skill sources</span>
        <span class="loader-connector">&#8594;</span>
        <span class="loader-step">scan SKILL.md</span>
        <span class="loader-connector">&#8594;</span>
        <span class="loader-step">advertise summary</span>
        <span class="loader-connector">&#8594;</span>
        <span class="loader-step">load via tool</span>
      </div>

      <div class="intervenes intervenes--skill">
        <span class="intervenes__label">How it loads</span>
        <p class="intervenes__when">Guidance lists available skills in context by name and description</p>
        <p class="intervenes__touches">The model calls the built-in <code>skill</code> tool to inject the chosen <code>SKILL.md</code></p>
        <span class="intervenes__direction">discovered upfront &middot; pulled on demand</span>
      </div>

      <p class="loader-card__note">Best for recurring playbooks, checklists, and domain habits inside one agent.</p>
      <a class="loader-card__link" href="https://github.com/sst/opencode/blob/dev/packages/core/src/skill.ts" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="loader-card__link-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#8599;</span>
        <span>See a real <code>SKILL.md</code> + the loader</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="loader-card loader-card--plugin">
      <div class="loader-card__header">
        <span class="loader-card__kicker">Runtime Hook Layer</span>
        <h3>Plugins</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="loader-card__text">
        OpenCode boots internal plugins and resolves configured plugin packages. Loaded plugins
        return hooks that receive mutable envelopes at model and tool boundaries.
      </p>
      <div class="loader-flow">
        <span class="loader-step">plugin config</span>
        <span class="loader-connector">&#8594;</span>
        <span class="loader-step">resolve + import</span>
        <span class="loader-connector">&#8594;</span>
        <span class="loader-step">return hooks</span>
        <span class="loader-connector">&#8594;</span>
        <span class="loader-step">mutate envelopes</span>
      </div>

      <div class="intervenes intervenes--plugin">
        <span class="intervenes__label">What a plugin can change</span>
        <div class="plugin-impact" aria-label="Plugin hook mutation surfaces">
          <div class="plugin-impact__row">
            <code>chat.params</code>
            <strong>Model input</strong>
            <span>temperature, max tokens, provider options before <code>llm.stream(request)</code></span>
          </div>
          <div class="plugin-impact__row">
            <code>tool.definition</code>
            <strong>Tool schema</strong>
            <span>description + parameters the model sees before it chooses tools</span>
          </div>
          <div class="plugin-impact__row">
            <code>tool.execute.before</code>
            <strong>Tool input</strong>
            <span>inspect, mutate, or guard args before the tool executes</span>
          </div>
          <div class="plugin-impact__row">
            <code>tool.execute.after</code>
            <strong>Tool output</strong>
            <span>truncate, annotate, or recover output before it re-enters context</span>
          </div>
          <div class="plugin-impact__row plugin-impact__row--wide">
            <code>experimental.text.complete</code>
            <strong>Model output</strong>
            <span>last chance to transform completed assistant text</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <span class="intervenes__direction">Examples: model fallback via <code>chat.params</code>; output compaction via <code>tool.execute.after</code></span>
      </div>

      <p class="loader-card__example">Think of a plugin as middleware around the model request and every tool call.</p>
      <p class="loader-card__note">Good for provider defaults, org integrations, review UX, and workflow-layer extensions.</p>
      <a class="loader-card__link" href="https://github.com/sst/opencode/blob/dev/packages/plugin/src/index.ts" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="loader-card__link-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#8599;</span>
        <span>See OpenCode&rsquo;s plugin hook contract</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
